elements.name: resource
comments: A known resource (a fragment of a stylesheet), stored in a repository,
that must be included in the generated artifact.

elements.name: rule

statements.name: call
statements.value: retval.push({ name: p.name() + '-' + p_nested.name(), value: p_nested.value() })

statements.name: call
statements.value: retval.push({ name: prop.wzTag + '-' + verify.replaceAll(attr, '_', '-'), value: prop[attr] })

comments: It has a child relation (one-to-many) with itself so one
can declare a tree of rules with unlimited deep.

elements.name: otherRuleSelector
comments: The wzName contains other selector(s) to add to those of the parent rule.
In case of a rule with many selectors allow the declaration on many nodes.

elements.name: otherClassSelector
comments: The wzName contains a class selector to add to those of the parent rule.

elements.name: property
comments: You should find a proper schema element that extends this one for every valid css3 property.
In any case this element is not abstract and can fit for missing properties.
In this case must contain a name-value pair separated by a blank: name is
the property name and value the property value.

elements.name: comment
comments: The wzName is the comment text.
